        tr
          td inputEl
          td HTMLElement<br>string
          td
          td Range Slider input element or CSS selector of input element. If not specified, will try to look for `input type="range"` inside of range slider element
        tr
          td dual
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enable dual range slider
        tr
          td step
          td number
          td 1
          td Minimal step between values
        tr
          td label
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables additional label around range slider knob
        tr
          td formatLabel
          td function(<span>value</span>)
          td
          td Method must return formatted range knob label text. As an argument it receives label value
        tr
          td min
          td number
          td
          td Minimum value
        tr
          td max
          td number
          td
          td Maximum value
        tr
          td value
          td number<br>array
          td
          td Initial value. Number in case of single range, and array of values in case of dual range
        tr
          td draggableBar
          td boolean
          td true
          td When enabled it is also possible to interact with range slider (change value) on range bar click and swipe.
        tr
          td vertical
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables vertical range slider
        tr
          td verticalReversed
          td boolean
          td false
          td Makes vertical range slider reversed (`vertical` must be also enabled)
        tr
          td scale
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables range slider scale
        tr
          td scaleSteps
          td number
          td 5
          td Number of scale steps
        tr
          td scaleSubSteps
          td number
          td 0
          td Number of scale sub steps (each step will be divided by this value)
        tr
          td formatScaleLabel
          td function (<span>value</span>)
